{
  "text": "Blood pressure should be monitored at each office visit (TABLE 1) . The goal for adults with diabetes should be to reduce blood pressure to 130/80 mm Hg. Reduction beyond this level may be associated with an increased mortality rate. [CITATION_1] Very high blood pressure (> 180 mm Hg systolic) should be lowered slowly. Lowering blood pressure delays the progression from microalbuminuria (30-299 mg/day or 20-199 \u03bcg/min) to macroalbuminuria (> 300 mg/day or > 200 \u03bcg/min) and slows the progression to renal failure.",
